item.title: 1991 fender strat
item.description:
@202685 wrote:

[quote=“Wet Dreamss, post:55, topic:445640”][quote author=Whackatre link=topic=548476.msg4022504#msg4022504 date=1340122742]

Wah wah pedal eww.

fix’t.

They’re actually pretty cool, if you don’t practice with one, you’ll go to extremes with it. Meaning, instead of doing a natural whammy, you could do an entire 12 fret jump.

You might as well buy an electric keyboard / electronic organ. Plug it into a Marshall with full overdrive, and then use the pitch bend for hacks.

I wanted a keyboard with +2/-24, too bad my Casio doesn’t support that.
[/quote]
except that would be playing a keyboard instead of a guitar…[/quote]

item.title: 1991 fender strat
item.dc:creator: @Native1 Native^
item.description:
@Native1 wrote:

[quote=“202685, post:33, topic:445640”][quote author=Wet Dreamss link=topic=548476.msg4021304#msg4021304 date=1340043615]

I has mine Gibson SG Original and i lurb it.
[/quote][quote author=Wet Dreamss link=topic=548476.msg4021106#msg4021106 date=1340032017]

Gibson > Fender

mine is a Gibson.

I’m in love with it considering I play metal/hard rock/ classic rock

SG’s are nice enough, but you’re limited to what you can play imo. I’d rather have a range of guitars such as I do, but if I didn’t have the money, I’d take a strat before anything else.
[/quote]Liar, i can play anything that doesn’t require a Whammy just fine. For that i have http://www.google.com/products/catalog?hl=en&safe=off&q=esp+KH-602&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_cp.r_qf.,cf.osb&biw=1920&bih=955&um=1&ie=UTF-8&tbm=shop&cid=9106132014735906860&sa=X&ei=y0rfT61B7frhBPL2tJgK&ved=0CHMQ8wIwAg

I don’t really use the whammy, if I do use it, it’s through some Dire Straits seeing as Mark Knopfler originally used the whammy when recording lady writer and sultans of swing.

If I’m playing rock, I tend to use my Epiphone SG, the only difference to the gibson are the pickups, the right amp/pedal can change that.

Whammy = wah pedal?

I have a Boss ME-25, the wah pedal can do a lot more insane things over the whammy bar, also, a whammy tends to throw a guitar of tune really fast.

speaking of out-of-tune… WHY THE SHIT DOES THE G STRING COME OUT OF TUNE SO FUCKING FAST! GAHH![/quote]
Happens often with new strings. Otherwise… Weird…

Read full topic
